President Obama announced his intent to nominate Elisebeth Collins Cook as a member of the Privacy and Civil Liberties Oversight Board. Cook is currently Counsel at Wilmer Cutler Pickering Hale and Dorr LLP and has been a member of the board since 2012. She has previous experience as Partner at Freeborn & Peters LLP, Republican Chief Counsel for Supreme Court Nominations for the U.S. Senate Judiciary Committee, and Assistant Attorney General for the Office of Legal Policy at the U.S. Department of Justice.

President Obama also announced his intent to nominate Mark McWatters as a member of the National Credit Union Administration Board. McWatters is currently the Assistant Dean for Graduate Programs and an adjunct professor at the Southern Methodist University Dedman School of Law. He has previous experience as counsel to U.S. Representative Jeb Hensarling, tax and mergers & acquisition counsel for HBK Capital Management, and partner at Patton Boggs and Fulbright & Jaworski. McWatters has also served on various boards and committees related to housing, technology, and oversight.